## 10. When you get stuck — comment Issue, do NOT bypass

Situations that warrant **STOP + comment** (do not try workaround):

| Situation | Action |
|---|---|
| Missing credential / permission | Comment Issue: "No permission for X. Blocked." |
| Persistent flaky test (>2 retries) | Comment Issue with test output. Architect/Pilot decides. Do NOT mark as skip. |
| Persistent fast-lane CI red | Comment Issue with run link + error. No force-push. |
| Merge conflict with `feat/<slug>` (another wave task merged first) | `git fetch origin && git rebase origin/feat/<slug>`. If conflict, comment Issue. Do NOT resolve large conflicts alone. |
| Architectural decision outside T-file scope | Comment Issue. Architect opens new ADR via separate task. Do NOT invent design. |
| Pre-existing bug blocks | Invoke `Skill superpowers:systematic-debugging` (ranked hypotheses, do NOT guess). Comment conclusion on Issue. |
| Migration SQL requested by T-file but you don't know current schema | READ `<your migrations path>/` in reverse chronological order to understand current state. If still uncertain, comment Issue. Do NOT invent a column (A14). |
| `feat/<feat-slug>` does not exist in `origin` | Comment Issue. Do NOT create — architect responsibility. |
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` expired / `gh` CLI auth failure | Comment Issue. Pilot rotates PAT. |

## 11. Environment — do NOT confuse DEV with PROD

If your project has a `supabase/config.toml` (or equivalent) pointing to PROD by default, **you must never run commands that affect PROD.**

| Command | Allowed? |
|---|---|
| Local-only commands (e.g. `supabase functions serve`, `pytest`, `npm test`) | yes |
| Local Docker (e.g. `supabase start`) | yes for integration tests |
| Push schema to remote DB (`supabase db push --linked` or equivalent) | **NEVER** |
| Deploy to prod (any deploy command) | **NEVER** |
| Apply migration via dashboard MCP | **NEVER** |
| Direct SQL access to PROD via MCP `execute_sql` | **NEVER** |

If T-file requests test against real DB: use the dev branch or local Docker. Before any push, confirm:

```bash
cat <your-config-pointing-to-current-target>
# Should show DEV or empty/local. If shows PROD, STOP.
```

## 12. TDD mandatory

```
RED -> GREEN -> REFACTOR -> VERIFY
```

| Phase | Action | Commit |
|---|---|---|
| **RED** | Write tests that fail for the right reasons (not import error). | `test(<scope>): scenarios <what>` |
| **GREEN** | Minimum code to make tests pass. | `<feat\|fix\|refactor>(<scope>): <what>` |
| **REFACTOR** | Cleanup, helper extraction if needed. **Only commit if real change.** | `refactor(<scope>): <what>` (optional) |
| **VERIFY** | `Skill superpowers:verification-before-completion`. Run lint + typecheck + relevant tests. **Capture output BEFORE marking `[x]`** in T-file. | (no new commit) |

Skipping RED phase = false regression test. **Never commit GREEN without RED commit before.**

## 13. Coverage >= 90% on touched files (auto-merge gate B item 4)

auto-merge.yml verifies that each production file changed has coverage >= 90%. **Skip:** diff only touches `*.md`, `*.test.*`, test directory.

If you can't reach 90% (e.g. error path nearly impossible to mock), **comment Issue** explaining — do NOT force PR without coverage. Architect decides if skip is justified or redesign needed.

