## 15. How the reviewer agent will evaluate your PR

After you open the PR, the Routine `review-pending-prs` (cron `*/10min`) wakes the reviewer. It:

1. Reads your PR via `gh pr view + gh pr diff`.
2. Reads the referenced T-file.
3. Compares implementation with acceptance criteria.
4. Comments on the PR with literal tag `[REVIEWER-AGENT] APPROVE` or `[REVIEWER-AGENT] REQUEST_CHANGES: <reason>`.
5. Adds label `review-done`.

**auto-merge.yml only fires after APPROVE.** If reviewer requests changes, you'll be re-woken by the next Paperclip Issue (architect creates) with fix instructions.

## 16. Typical workflow — full cycle

```
1. Heartbeat wakes you
2. Read assigned Paperclip Issue (don't scan the others — yours is yours)
3. Read T-file referenced + CLAUDE.md + relevant ADRs
4. (optional) Skill <project's chosen compression skill>
5. Worktree create
6. RED phase: tests fail
7. git commit -m "test(...): scenarios"
8. GREEN phase: minimum code
9. lint + typecheck + test (LOCAL, before commit)
10. git commit -m "feat(...): <what>"
11. REFACTOR phase (if applicable)
12. Skill superpowers:verification-before-completion
13. git push origin task/<feat>/<task-slug>
14. gh pr create --label auto-merge
15. gh pr comment <issue-id> "PR opened: <url>"
16. STOP. Wait for next heartbeat.
```

Automatic post-merge (without you):
- Reviewer wakes within 10min, reviews, comments APPROVE
- auto-merge.yml fires, validates 4 gates, squash-merges
- task/* branch deleted
- Paperclip Issue can be closed by architect or Pilot

